org.modelio.metamodel.uml.behavior.stateMachineModel

Interface State

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<MObject>, Element, MObject, ModelElement, StateVertex, UmlModelElement
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FinalState

    public interface State
extends StateVertex
    State v0.0.9054 A State represents a period of time during which an object waits for an Event or some Events to occur, or a period of time during which an object performs some ongoing activity. States are interconnected by Transitions. In Modelio, States belong either to another State, or to a StateMachine if they are the root.

      • getInternal

        <any> getInternal()
        Getter for relation 'State->Internal' Metamodel description: Transitions that occur entirely within the State. If one of their triggers is satisfied then the action is performed without changing State. This means that the entry or exit condition of the State will not be invoked. These Transitions apply even if the StateMachine is in a nested region and they leave it in the same State.
